The paper deals with the problem of tensor PCA, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithms proposed in the paper are based on statistical physics and related algorithms such as belief propagation and AMP, which are also relevant to the fields of data science (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper suggests a new approach for obtaining optimal algorithms for Bayesian inference problems, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
